        <title>Documenting your data model with liquibase, tbls &amp; jOOQ</title>
        <link rel="alternate" href="https://lorefnon.me/2021/08/07/Documenting-Your-Data-Model-With-Liquibase-and-Tbls/"/>
        <content type="html">&lt;p&gt;Documenting a database schema is often an afterthought, even though it is really important esp. for onboarding new developers into the project.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post outlines a really straightforward approach I recently adopted for my projects using &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.liquibase.org/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener external nofollow noreferrer&#34;&gt;Liquibase&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/k1LoW/tbls&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener external nofollow noreferrer&#34;&gt;tbls&lt;/a&gt; &amp;amp; &lt;a href=&#34;https://jooq.org/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener external nofollow noreferrer&#34;&gt;jOOQ&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;!-- more --&gt;

&lt;h1 id=&#34;About-Liquibase&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#About-Liquibase&#34; class=&#34;headerlink&#34; title=&#34;About Liquibase&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;About Liquibase&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;Liquibase is a great utility for managing database schema evolution. It has support for a great set of features like a YAML&amp;#x2F;XML DSL that takes care of automatic rollbacks, support for parameter interpolation, and many more which are quite handy in enterprise contexts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here is what the DSL looks like in YAML: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;hljs&#34;&gt;&lt;table class=&#34;hlcode-table&#34;&gt;&lt;tr style=&#34;border:none;&#34; class=&#34;hlcode-line  &#34; &gt;&lt;td style=&#34;border:none&#34; class=&#34;hlcode-code-cell&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;hljs-bullet&#34;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;hljs-attr&#34;&gt;changeSet:&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr style=&#34;border:none;&#34; class=&#34;hlcode-line  &#34; &gt;&lt;td style=&#34;border:none&#34; class=&#34;hlcode-code-cell&#34;&gt;    &lt;span class=&#34;hljs-attr&#34;&gt;id:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;hljs-number&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr style=&#34;border:none;&#34; class=&#34;hlcode-line  &#34; &gt;&lt;td style=&#34;border:none&#34; class=&#34;hlcode-code-cell&#34;&gt;    &lt;span class=&#34;hljs-attr&#34;&gt;author:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;hljs-string&#34;&gt;lorefnon&lt;/span&gt;
